news.title: Punjab cabinet approves reduction in interest on enhancement from allottees
news.para: ​The rate of interest to be charged on the enhancement recoverable will be reduced from 15 per cent to 7.5 per cent. This decision was taken in the cabinet meeting chaired by Chief Minister Charanjit Singh.

news.title: Rajasthan: 1.29 lakh PMAY-Gramin houses incomplete, officials to face action
news.para: Also, all the districts have been directed to complete construction of the remaining houses by December 31, 2021, stated the letter written to the districts by rural development department secretary Krishna Kant Pathak.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA disposed of 90% complaints from home buyers this year
news.para: This state is at the third position in the country to resolve the problems of the home-buyers. An official said, "The Rajasthan RERA received 1,484 complaints till Diwali, which were redressed by the authority."

news.title: Experion to invest $300 million in student housing
news.para: “We plan to open our first property in the next academic year, which will begin in June 2022,” said BK Malagi, CEO and board member of Experion Developers. “We’ll go with an asset-heavy approach in which we own and operate the property.”

news.title: Mumbai: 100-year-old chawl will make way for 36-storey tower
news.para: The state’s housing authority, Mhada, gave the go-ahead on October 27 to redevelop Old Chikhalwadi at Tardeo. The 1.54-acre plot comprising a labyrinth of 12 chawls, in which over 200 people live, stands behind Bhatia Hospital.

news.title: Gurugram: DHBVN issues notices to eight builders over failure to develop power infra
news.para: The Dakshin Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam (DHBVN) has recently issued notices to all the defaulters, giving them two-week time to take corrective steps for developing the required infra.

news.title: DLF Cyber City Developers' net debt up 3% to Rs 19,640 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: According to an investors presentation, the net debt of DCCDL rose to Rs 19,640 crore as on September 30, 2021 from Rs 19,072 crore at the end of the first quarter of this fiscal year.

news.title: MahaRERA directs builders to reveal mortgage status of housing projects
news.para: The move is aimed at improving transparency and alerting prospective homebuyers about any mortgage or loans taken by the developer against the apartments they are about to buy - or the project itself.

news.title: Sale of forfeited land valid if proceedings are dropped: Karnataka HC
news.para: The Nelamangala tahsildar has now been directed to effect mutation and revenue entries in favour of the petitioner in 30 days.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh CM hands over 426 houses under flood relief scheme
news.para: Chief minister Chouhan inaugurated 426 houses constructed under the Mukhyamantri Flood Relief Housing scheme in 40 villages of Budhni tehsil from village Somalwada and conducted a virtual ‘grih pravesh’ of the beneficiaries.

news.title: Maharashtra: Slum dwellers can sell houses after demolition in five years with SRA nod
news.para: Earlier, people could sell their tenement only 10 years after the building was completed, and now they can do so within five years after demolition with the SRA's permission, he said.

news.title: Hyderabad: 43 illegal buildings on government land razed in Gopanpally
news.para: The drive was carried out by the radial roads division of the roads and buildings department to make way for six radial roads in the area.

news.title: PNB Housing's Q2 disbursement up 68% over Q1: Hardayal Prasad, MD
news.para: "In terms of the collection efficiency, we are at 98.6% which is almost pre Covid levels and far better than last quarter which was 96.6%."

news.title: Mumbai: High-rise buildings & narrow roads creating hurdles for fire brigades
news.para: For those on the 40th floor and beyond, the building’s internal systems will have to kick in on time before they can be evacuated amidst a blaze or a short circuit.

news.title: Hyderabad: NGT panel finds Ameenpur nalas encroached
news.para: The joint committee has also recommended immediate cancellation of construction permission granted to Lalitha Constructions and others.
